Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph

SpineDigest CLI

Purpose:
  Create and operate portable Wiki Graph archives for AI agents.
  Treat `.wikg` as the managed archive. Use commands to mutate or inspect it; do not edit archive internals directly.

Object model:
  Search and navigation return URI-addressable objects. URI forms are explicitly classified as scope or object URIs.
  Read `wikigraph help uri` before choosing a target.

Object workflow:
  - Scope URIs enumerate objects by default.
  - Scope URIs with `--query <query>` search within that scope.
  - Object URIs open one readable object by default.
  - `related` expands from one URI to nearby URIs.
  - `evidence` traces a URI to source-backed evidence.
  - `pack` builds bounded Agent-readable context around one graph object URI.

Object commands:
  wikigraph <scope-uri> [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <scope-uri> --query <query> [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <object-uri> [--evidence [n]] [--context <n>] [--backlinks] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <entity|triple|summary|chunk-uri> evidence [--query <query>] [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <chunk-uri|entity-uri> related [--query <query>] [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--role <any|subject|object|self>] [--evidence [n]] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <located-chunk-uri|located-entity-uri> pack [--budget <chars>] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph next <cursor> [--limit <n>] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph next <wikigraph-uri-with-wikg-locator> <cursor> [--limit <n>] [--json|--jsonl]

URI requirement:
  URI-addressed commands use Wiki Graph URIs, not bare filesystem paths.
  Read `wikigraph help uri` before using these commands; skipping the URI rules commonly leads to invalid commands.

Archive commands:
  wikigraph <archive-uri> create [source] [--input-format <format>] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]
  wikigraph <archive-uri> export --output-format <format> [--output <path>]
  wikigraph <archive-uri> inspect
  wikigraph transform [--input <path>] [--output <path>] [--input-format <format>] [--output-format <format>] [--digest-dir <path>] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>] [--stage <stage>] [--verbose|-v]

Generation jobs:
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input <chapter-uri> --task <reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph> --accept-cost [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]
  wikigraph wikg://local/job [--all] [--active]
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> [--json]
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> watch [--jsonl] [--from beginning|now]
  Generation jobs call an LLM, consume tokens, and may incur provider charges.

Maintenance:
  wikigraph <archive-uri> [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <archive-uri> set [metadata options] [--llm <json>]
  wikigraph <cover-uri>
  wikigraph <chapter-collection-uri> add [options]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/state [--json]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> move|remove|reset [options]
  wikigraph <object-uri>/meta [--json]
  wikigraph <object-uri>/meta set|put|delete|clear
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/source set [text] [--input <path>] --input-format <format>
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/summary set [text] [--input <path>]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/title set <title>
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/title clear
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter/tree
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter/tree set [options]
  wikigraph gc [--force] [--dry-run] [--json]
  wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm
  wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm set|put|delete|clear|test
  wikigraph wikg://local/config/concurrent
  wikigraph wikg://local/config/concurrent set|put|delete|clear
  wikigraph wikg://local/config/wikispine
  wikigraph wikg://local/config/wikispine set|put|delete|clear|test
  wikigraph help [topic] [--help|-h]

Help contract:
  - Use `wikigraph <uri> --help` to inspect a URI command, its default behavior, and supported predicates.
  - Use `wikigraph <uri> <predicate> --help` to inspect a URI-bound predicate command.
  - Use `wikigraph <non-predicate-command> --help` for non-predicate commands such as `transform`, `gc`, `legacy`, and `next`.
  - Use `wikigraph help <topic>` for cross-command concepts, constraints, and runtime behavior.
  - Treat `wikigraph --help` as the root page of the same help system.
  - Use `wikigraph legacy migrate --help` only when upgrading an `.sdpub` archive.

